remarks: Started raining before we could finish
Vial 1 has 532 of the 1639 larval ticks, in a 10 ml vial in RNA solution. The other 1107 larval ticks were discarded. The 7 nymph ticks are in a cryo vial with RNA stabilization buffer

Vial 1: 12 nymphs, 1 larval in RNA stabilization solution. Vial 2: 36 nymphs, 508 larvals. Ticks in vial 2 were stored in 95% ethanol then transferred to RNA stabilization solution. Due to the large number, some ticks (at least 1, but up to 3-5 nymphs) escaped during collection by falling off the tick cloth.
Due to time constraints, this plot was measured and recorded by 2 teams of 2. Each team measured 80 meters.
Vial 1 consists of nymph ticks only. Vial 2 has 500 of 1469 larval ticks which were stored in EtOH and then transferred to RNA
8 larvals in vial 1 collected in RNA. 525 larvals in vial 2 collected in EtOH and moved to RNA
Collected in EtOH and moved to RNA
